1 AN ACT concerning water; establishing the water program task force to
2 evaluate the state's water program and funding for such program;
3 requiring the task force to establish a water planning working group
4 and submit a report to the legislature and the governor.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. (a) There is hereby established the water program task
8 force. The task force shall consist of the following 13 voting members:
9 (1) The chair of the house of representatives committee on water or
10 the chair's designee;
11 (2) the chair of the house of representatives committee on agriculture
12 and natural resources or the chair's designee;
13 (3) the chair of the senate committee on agriculture and natural
14 resources or the chair's designee;
15 (4) the ranking minority member of the house of representatives
16 committee on water or the ranking member's designee;
17 (5) the ranking minority member of the senate agriculture and natural
18 resources committee or the ranking member's designee;
19 (6) one member of the house of representatives who does not sit on
20 the committee on water or the committee on agriculture and natural
21 resources appointed by the speaker of the house of representatives;
22 (7) one member of the senate who does not sit on the committee on
23 agriculture and natural resources appointed by the president of the senate;
24 and
25 (8) six Kansas residents jointly appointed by the speaker of the house
26 of representatives and the president of the senate.
27 (b) Each member of the task force who is not a member of the
28 legislature shall represent at least one of the following stakeholders:
29 (1) A Kansas employer with a vested water right;
30 (2) a commercial user of a municipal or industrial water right;
31 (3) an agricultural producer;
32 (4) an economic development organization;
33 (5) a water utility;
34 (6) a resident Kansas Indian tribe, Potawatomi, Kickapoo, Iowa or
35 Sac and Fox;
36 (7) a rural water district;

